"> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufalorsavageheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falor Savageheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/27/02 8:56:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another damn Epic question!!??!?!</span><hr size=1> I've been in the hole more times than I have wished, and I've done both ways :P<br>
<br>
As far as CoHing people.  There's a ledge next to kirn's tower with no roamers that is right next to the big hole.  <br>
<br>
Strategy there is to have a brell cleric that can revive have revive, DA, and ITU up on spell list.  Cast sow and see invis on the cleric.  Cleric casts DA on the ledge in Panieel where the big &quot;hole&quot; is and jumps in.  Cleric zones in untouched to a non-agro area at the bottom of the hole.  <br>
<br>
A brell rogue hide/snuck the whole way down to the bottom (because even brell followers are KoS to the ghosts) of the hole.  Got to the cleric (or more efficient, was already waiting for the cleric to zone in), guides the cleric up the long path to  kirns tower.  <br>
<br>
When you encounter to static rock golems near kirns tower, ITU up on the cleric and have the rogue have hide/sneak on.  Rogue shows cleric the ledge where he will remain towards the back between the 2 rocks waiting for a mage body to come to him.  (All of this is assuming the cleric does not know where his revive station is).<br>
<br>
A CoH mage is setup in a group.  Group leader is a person that has a nice connection and will probably not go LD (even if they do, it's not a total disaster).  Group leader invites a bard (if you have one), the CoH mage. <br>
<br>
Rogue goes outside to get SoW, comes back in.  Someone duels the mage.  Mage /consents the rogue and the rogue runs like hell to the cleric to revive the body.  Mage gets revived and CoH's the bard.  Group leader invites a chanter, and a cleric.  Cleric is bound outside the hole (incase group leader goes LD).  CoH chanter/cleric and you should be set and continue to invite people to get CoH'd. <br>
<br>
In event of LD.  Cleric forms the group up with the mage next to kirns tower (inviting the bard(s), and mage), and gates back to the bind spot (right outside the hole).  Cleric continues the CoH chain.  First to get CoH'd is someone who binded themselves outside the hole incase that cleric goes LD.  Get the picture?<br>
<br>
Not too complicated.  Done it a couple times without a problem.  All you would need to do is ITU all the groups, run up to Kirns tower and and kill kirn.  This is an efficient way as far as time is concerned.<br>
<br>
If you want the satisfaction of doing it the way the quest was &quot;intended&quot; on being done, fight the whole way through.  Done that too :P  It's also fun, but requires more time than the CoH chain.  Extra benefits are the possibility of getting good armor drops (the IGS, ISP, etc) and knowing you fought you way to kirn to get your next epic piece.<br>
<br>
<br>
Whatever you do, good luck.  Like I said, I've done both, and I've had more fun fighting my way through :P<br>
<br>
If I forgot something on the CoH chain part, don't come yelling to me :P <p>Falor<br>
